(thirdQuint)Dietary Anthocyanins Improve Glucose and Lipid Metabolism in a Dose - Dependent Manner.

 In order to study the effect of anthocyanins on the improvement of glucose and lipid metabolism, randomized controlled trials were conducted to enrolled 300 patients with dyslipidemia.

 The subjects were divided into 0 mg / d, 40 mg / d, 80 mg / d, 160 mg / d, 320 mg/ d five dose groups, intervention for 12 weeks, comparing different doses of anthocyanins on glucose and lipid metabolism.

To explore the best dose of anthocyanins for the prevention and treatment of anthocyanin metabolic diseases provide an important scientific basis.

